CatDescriptText: Mrs. Florence Peterson, housewife, McDonald, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that we are spending too much money for foreign aid? Do you think that what we have spent has halted the spread of communism?" answer reads: "It seems that the money which we have spent for foreign aid has not shown any results.  We should put our trust in God and spend more money at home on our needs, and that way we will be better off."
